heavy rain from the remnants of hurricane jerry triggered 
flooding in the appalachians tuesday closing roads and schools and 
forcing evacuations in west virginia and kentucky rain fell across 
much of the rest of the east 
up to 4 inches of rain fell on southern west virginia schools 
were closed in four counties because rising water threatened to 
block school buses 
flooding on the tug fork of the big sandy river along the west 
virginiakentucky line would be the first test of the west 
williamson floodwall which was dedicated just this summer a 
floodwall protecting downtown williamson is less than 60 percent 
complete 
the tug fork rose 3 feet an hour tuesday afternoon the river 
crested 6 feet above its banks at matewan early in the evening and 
was expected to crest 3 feet above flood stage at williamson 
overnight the national weather service reported 
floodwaters swept away an unoccupied house along the river in 
boone county officials said 
people from lowlying rural areas near matewan and in williamson 
were asked to leave their homes officials said about 150 people 
were evacuated 
in southeastern kentucky where 4 to 6 inches of rain fell in 
the 18 hours ended at 1 pm tuesday many roads were flooded or 
blocked by mudslides the weather service said fastrising creeks 
forced evacuations in pike floyd clay and jackson counties 
more than 760 students and faculty at mcdowell elementary and 
high school saw frasure and left beaver creeks spill over their 
banks and flood school buildings with up to 3 feet of water early 
tuesday 
rain showers and occasional thunderstorms during the afternoon 
extended over much of new england new york state northern and 
eastern pennsylvania new jersey maryland much of virginia west 
virginia ohio kentucky southern indiana and southern illinois 
showers and thunderstorms also reached from western georgia 
across the florida panhandle alabama southern mississippi 
southeastern louisiana and along the lower texas gulf coast 
scattered snow showers fell from northcentral wyoming to 
southcentral colorado but no measurable amounts were reported 
during the six hours up to 2 pm edt at dawn there was an inch of 
snow on the ground in denver cheyenne wyo and limon colo 
freeze warnings through wednesday morning were posted for 
sections of colorado kansas missouri and oklahoma overnight 
lows near freezing were expected in the texas panhandle and 
northeastern new mexico 
by contrast a record high temperature for the date was set in 
cape hatteras nc where it was 83 degrees records were also set 
in orlando fla where it was 93 and jacksonville fla where it 
was 91 
temperatures around the nation at 3 pm edt ranged from 32 
degrees at custer sd to 98 at palm springs calif tuesdays 
low for the lower 48 states was 11 in west yellowstone mont 
