victory over republican tom anderson in a special congressional 
election tuesday giving the democrats all five of mississippis 
us house seats for the first time in 17 years 
with all 372 precincts reporting in the race to pick a successor 
to the late us rep larkin smith taylor had 83093 votes or 65 
percent to 44430 or 35 percent for anderson a veteran 
washington aide 
the gop which holds both of mississippis us senate seats 
lost its only house seat which it had held since 1972 smith a 
republican died in a small plane crash in august 
taylor carried all but one of the 12 counties in the 5th 
district in mississippis southeastern corner which includes the 
gulf coast and the cities of biloxi gulfport and hattiesburg 
