medicare will have to cover the 2092 percent themselves 
medicare is taking a total 17 billion cut while defense 
spending accounted for a 81 billion reduction 
medicaid payments to states are exempt from the budget cuts as 
are social security supplemental security income and aid to 
families with dependent children 
sally christensen director of budget service for the education 
department said the student loan program is the only education 
program immediately affected by the budget cuts 
the law raises the loan origination fee from 5 percent to 55 
percent and cuts the special allowance payment to lending 
institutions from 325 percent to 3 percent ms christensen said 
with these changes banks will make less of a profit and students 
will pay more for taking out a loan 
dennis kaplan chief of budget control and analysis for the 
agriculture department said it is widely believed there that 
congress will soon work out a budget agreement to replace the 
automatic cuts 
if not he said the food safety and inspection service will 
probably furlough a lot of their employees but that wont occur 
until august or september of next year 
the same would be true of the forest service and farmers home 
administration he said 
much of the agriculture departments spending is exempt from the 
cuts including food stamps school lunches and other child 
nutrition programs 
at the federal aviation administration which oversees 16800 
air traffic controllers spokesman john leyden said there would be 
no immediate impact other than pulling back on hirings 
procurements and changes of status for personnel 
the white house office of management and budget said a prolonged 
impasse might force the layoff of air traffic controllers for three 
days a month and a reduction in military forces by 160000 
