<TEXT>
the devastating earthquake that killed 
hundreds in northern california vividly recalls the catastrophic 
quake and fire that laid waste to san francisco in 1906 
quakes are almost commonplace in california with that state and 
western nevada experiencing 90 percent of the tremors recorded in 
this country according to the us geological survey 
but when the rare major quake comes as it did in the nations 
seconddeadliest quake on tuesday serious damage can result as 
well as death and injury 
and while the west coast feels the earth shake more often 
shocks can strike any part of the nation 
the new quake registered at 69 on the richter scale and was on 
the notorious san andreas fault that reading made it the 
sixthmost powerful quake to strike california this century and 
the mos powerful since a 70 quake centered in eureka in 1980 
such a quake can cause severe damage with each increase of one 
whole number meaning an increase of 10 times in strength 
tuesdays devastating quake still is well short of the 1906 san 
francisco quake however which was estimated at 83 on the scale 
that disaster killed more than 700 people largely in fires which 
swept the city in the wake of the tremor 
california and alaska are subject to many quakes because they 
rest on what is called the ring of fire a region of volcanoes and 
earthquakeprone lands circling the pacific ocean 
this ring is caused by the movement of the giant plates that 
underlie the land and oceans of the earth plates move gradually 
stresses build up over time and then are released in quakes 
san francisco sits astride the san andreas fault a crack in the 
earth where the pacific plate is slowly sliding north compared with 
the rest of california which rests on the north american plate it 
was the same fault that instigated the 1906 tremor 
while the 1906 disaster is burned into american memory this 
country has been relatively fortunate compared to other nations 
in terms of earthquake disasters 
the 25000 deaths reported in armenia a year ago are fresh in 
memory and china had an estimated 650000 deaths in a violent 
quake in 1976 japan too has suffered many deaths in historic 
quakes as have iran turkey nicaragua peru chile and other 
nations 
the 1906 san francisco quake was the largest american death 
toll although at least two other events were stronger in terms of 
the richter scale 
here is a rundown of other major earthquakes in american history 
as recorded by the us geological survey 
new madrid mo was shaken by three quakes in 18111812 
estimated at 84 to 87 on the richter scale but damage and 
casualties were light because the region had a relatively small 
population at the time these quakes were felt as far away as 
boston and new york 
prince william sound alaska was pounded by a quake rated at 
84 on the richter scale on march 27 1964 in this century only 
one quake in chile in 1960 has been stronger there were 131 
deaths and extensive damage in alaska 
on nov 18 1867 the virgin islands were shaken by a magnitude 
75 quake also felt in puerto rico and the dominican republic 
waves as large as 20 feet were generated 
in the same area a 75 temblor shook the mona passage near 
puerto rico on oct 11 1918 some 116 people died many in the 
giant wave generated by the quake 
on aug 17 1959 a quake rated at 73 struck hebgen lake 
mont and was felt from seattle to north dakota to utah extensive 
damage was reported and 28 people died 
olympia wash was struck by a 71 quake on april 13 1949 
killing eight people and causing extensive damage in washington and 
oregon 
there was a quake rated 70 at borah peak idaho on oct 25 
1983 it was widely felt but only two people were killed 
coalinga calif was the focus of a 67 magnitude quake on may 
2 1983 injuring 45 people and causing 31 million in damage 
on aug 31 1886 charleston sc suffered a 66 magnitude 
quake killing 60 people this tremor was felt as far away as 
boston milwaukee and havana cuba 
a quake measured at 66 also did severe damage to the san 
fernando valley of california on feb 9 1971 killing 65 people 
</TEXT>
