pm followed two minutes later by a 60second news report by ted 
koppel anchor of abcs nightline 
in contrast nbcs first quake bulletin read from washington by 
correspondent katherine couric didnt air until 831 pm it 
wasnt until after 9 pm that nbc joined its rivals in airing 
pictures from the scene 
it wasnt the happiest night for nbc anchor tom brokaw early in 
his reports when quake casualty figures were rising he said 40 
people had been reported killed in one freeway collapse and more 
than 50 in another 
the latter report proved erroneous brokaw subsquently corrected 
himself on the air an nbc spokeswoman said 
in an action reminiscent of september 1985 when brokaw rather 
and world news tonight anchor peter jennings of abc anchored 
their broadcasts from quakestricken mexico city all three flew to 
san francisco to anchor their programs there 
each of the three men also anchored a onehour primetime 
special on the san francisco earthquake wednesday 
rather also will anchor a 48 hours earthquake special 
thursday night abcs sam donaldson will also be in san francisco 
that night coanchoring his half of the primetime live news 
series abc said 
nbcs today starting a threeday visit in chicago when the 
quake hit will broadcast from san francisco on thursday and friday 
with the second quakecaused postponement of game three of the 
world series announced wednesday abcs schedule for that night 
shifted from baseball to four sitcoms normally shown on wednesday 
jennings earthquake special bumped a series on abc china 
beach 
abc had no comment on how much it might lose in advertising 
revenue because of postponements of the world series 
one madison avenue executive richard kostrya estimated that it 
could total 10 million a night for each night the series is 
postponed he said his figures represent the amount he estimates 
regular programming earns 
a postponed series game when finally broadcast displaces a 
