stock market crash 
they kept pushing as the day went on donald selkin head of 
stockindex futures research at prudentialbache securities inc 
said tuesday the programs id say were a good part of the 
advance 
the practice of moving millions of shares of stock with 
lightning speed was voluntarily limited by stock exchanges and 
brokerage houses in the wake of the oct 19 1987 crash but 
gradually has been revived this year 
after fridays 190point decline some analysts speculated that 
the new york stock exchange over the weekend encouraged firms to 
avoid using computerized sell programs that could spur a 
disastrous plunge but to step in with buy orders if possible that 
could propel the market higher the exchange declined to comment on 
the matter tuesday 
program trading is a strategy involving the stockindex futures 
market in chicago and stock trading in new york stockindex 
futures are contracts to buy or sell baskets of stocks at specified 
prices by a specified date 
in one form called index arbitrage the strategy employs 
computers to buy and sell huge blocks of stocks and index futures 
in an attempt to profit from minute differences in prices on the 
two markets the practice can cause rapid price swings and is 
believed by some to have accelerated the 1987 market collapse 
but defenders complain that the strategy is used as a scapegoat 
for sometimenormal market fluctuations 
theres always fish in a tidal wave because theres always 
fish in the water said r steven wunsch vice president of 
financial futures at kidder peabody amp co one of wall streets 
heaviest program trading firms 
buyers and sellers in an outright fashion move markets he 
said those who are buying and selling simultaneously dont cause 
volatility taken all together its a noninfluence 
wunsch instead blamed market volatility on an overdependence on 
intermediate dealers whose job is to bring together buyers and 
sellers 
a presidential task force known as the brady commission that 
invesigated the 1987 crash concluded that index arbitagers were 
active at times of big price swings but didnt cause the crash 
after the crash some firms reduced their program trading levels 
because of intense criticism by politicians and others dean 
witter reynolds inc abandoned the practice altogether but there 
has been a revival this year officials said 
the sharp price swings friday and monday intensified debate over 
index arbitrage nyse chairman john j phelan jr said program 
trading accounted for 24 million of 100 million shares traded in 
the final 1 hours of trading friday 
we would say that it was abundant but we wouldnt say it was 
something that precipitated the market decline he said 
when the markets opened monday stockindex futures were trading 
at a discount to the underlying stocks stock prices sank in the 
first halfhour of trading buying of major market index futures of 
the 20 stocks soon pulled the futures market higher and buy 
programs kicked in a similar action triggered buying on terrible 
tuesday oct 20 1987 
some players said wall streets major brokerages should step in 
with programs to help stem a decline 
i think they should be in there all the time taking the market 
up said john j cramer president of the new york money 
management firm cramer amp co whenever the big sell programs come 
in i think the powers that be ought to be in there taking it back 
up 
</TEXT>
