television and cable systems elsewhere in the southeast 
golden west chief executive ron redfern said the papers have a 
combined circulation of 487000 and gross annual revenues of about 
15 million 
he would not disclose the asking price but said that weekly 
newspapers usually sell for one to two times their gross revenues 
a number of companies had expressed interest redfern said but 
he declined not identify them 
golden west was formed in 1980 and 1981 with the purchase of 
several small weekly newspaper chains redfern said the company 
initially had planned to convert one or more of the papers to 
dailies but later changed its plans 
media general successfully defended itself against a hostile 
takeover attempt last year by hollywood producer burt sugarman and 
sold its only other west coast operation a paper mill in pomona 
to sugarman after his bid failed 
