mesa airlines inc said wednesday that 
stateswest airlines inc had offered 153 million in cash and 
securities for all the common stock in mesa that the phoenixbased 
airline doesnt already own 
the offer values the entire company at 165 million 
gary risley mesas vice president for corporate affairs said 
stateswest is offering 10 7 a share in cash plus stateswest 
securities with a value of 3 per share for each mesa share 
the offer was made in a letter to mesa from stateswest chairman 
rudy miller stateswest had asked mesas board of directors to keep 
the terms confidential but mesa announced the terms wednesday 
risley said mesa has 165 million shares of stock stateswest 
acquired 725 percent of the stock in may and miller said tuesday 
he had purchased a little stock in the last couple of days but 
declined to say how much 
risley said tuesday the stateswest proposal would be referred to 
mesas board for consideration along with recommendations from 
mesas financial and legal advisers 
we believe that the terms we have proposed are fair and 
generous and in the best interest of the mesa shareholders 
miller said tuesday in announcing the proposal 
because we are making this offer on a friendly basis we are 
first submitting it to the board of directors for its review and 
consideration miller said 
we hope to have the opportunity to discuss the proposal with 
mesas board of directors in the near future he said 
last week mesa officials said they had no interest in a 
friendly takeover proposal by stateswest and later in the week 
