gains 
the bond market is still taking its cues from stock market 
fluctuations and i expect that will continue for awhile said 
mickey levy chief economist for first fidelity bancorporation of 
lawrenceville nj 
he said bond traders feel that if stocks fall sharply the 
federal reserve is likely to encourage lower interest rates a 
positive development for bonds 
but he said bond traders are likely to begin paying less 
attention to gyrations in the stock market and focus more on 
prospects for the economy 
other analysts said the dollars decline in foreign exchange 
trading and the prospect of new borrowing by the federal government 
