wang laboratories inc reported an expected 
firstquarter loss wednesday as the struggling computer maker 
showed the effects of a slowdown in the computer industry 
wang officials reported a firstquarter net loss wednesday of 
621 million or 38 cents per share compared with net earnings of 
131 million or 8 cents per share during the same period last 
year 
the latest quarters loss includes a 129 million pretax 
restructuring charge to cover the costs of employee severance 
packages the yearearlier quarter included a 31 million loss 
from discontinued operations 
revenue for the first quarter was 5968 million down almost 13 
percent from a restated 684 million during the same period last 
year wang officials reported 
the first quarters results should not be a surprise to 
anyone and certainly there will be another loss in the second 
quarter said richard w miller wangs president and chief 
operating officer 
however he said he expected the company to return to 
profitability in its fourth fiscal quarter which ends next june 
</TEXT>
