<TEXT>
northrop corp said wednesday its 
thirdquarter profit fell 23 percent due in part to a decline in 
research and development work on such projects as the b2 stealth 
bomber 
northrop the focus of repeated investigations and much 
congressional criticism for its performance on various government 
contracts in recent years said it earned 215 million or 46 
cents per share for the three months ending sept 30 compared 
with a profit of 288 million or 61 cents per share in the same 
period a year ago 
sales for the third quarter totaled 125 billion down from 
136 billion a year earlier 
the los angelesbased company said the b2 which some in 
congress want to kill as too expensive has passed the peak of its 
development phase and is now in initial production at a low rate 
the defense contractor which lost 781 million in the second 
quarter also noted that it had made fewer deliveries of its fa18 
fighters 
interest expense in the third quarter was 35 million 18 
million higher than in the same quarter last year debt at sept 30 
was 122 billion compared to 911 million a year earlier 
northrop stock closed down 25 cents at 2112 a share wednesday 
in composite trading on the new york stock exchange that put the 
companys stocks market value below 1 billion a very low level 
for a company with yearly revenues in the 6 billion range 
</TEXT>
